---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../../../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import CTAButton from '../../../components/CTAButton.astro';
import { COMPANY_INFO } from '../../../utils/constants';

const lang = 'en';
const post = {
  title: 'Isuzu vs Fuso Prime Mover 2026: Which Brand for Your Transport Business?',
  slug: 'isuzu-vs-fuso-prime-mover-2026',
  excerpt: 'Compare Isuzu vs Fuso prime movers for your transport business. Finance with 0% down payment. Features, reliability, and ROI comparison.',
  date: '2026-01-08',
  author: 'Ing Heng Credit Team',
  readTime: 7,
  category: 'Transport Vehicles',
  image: '/images/blog/prime-mover-financing.jpg'
};

const keywords = ['isuzu vs fuso', 'prime mover comparison', 'truck financing', '0% down payment', 'transport business'],
  breadcrumbItems = [
  { label: 'Home', href: '/en' },
  { label: 'Blog', href: '/en/blog' },
  { label: post.title, href: `/en/blog/${post.slug}` }
];
---

<BaseLayout title={post.title} description={post.excerpt} lang={lang} keywords={keywords}>
  <script type="application/ld+json">
    {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "BlogPosting",
      "headline": post.title,
      "description": post.excerpt,
      "datePublished": post.date,
      "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": post.author },
      "publisher": {
        "@type": "Organization",
        "name": "Ing Heng Credit & Leasing Sdn Bhd",
        "logo": {
          "@type": "ImageObject",
          "url": "https://inghengcredit.com/logo.png"
        }
      }
    }
  </script>

  <Breadcrumbs items={breadcrumbItems} />

  <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <header class="mb-8">
      <span class="text-sm font-semibold" style="color: #D4A574;">Transport Vehicles</span>
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mt-2" style="color: #2D1810; font-family: 'Bebas Neue', sans-serif; text-transform: uppercase;">{post.title}</h1>
      <p class="text-gray-600 mt-4">{post.excerpt}</p>
      <div class="flex items-center gap-4 text-sm text-gray-500 mt-4">
        <span>{post.author}</span>
        <span>•</span>
        <time>{new Date(post.date).toLocaleDateString('en-US', { year: 'numeric', month: 'long', day: 'numeric' })}</time>
        <span>•</span>
        <span>{post.readTime} min read</span>
      </div>
    </header>

    <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
      <h2>Isuzu vs Fuso: Malaysia's Popular Prime Movers</h2>

      <p>Choosing between Isuzu and Fuso prime movers affects your transport business for years. Both brands dominate Malaysian roads. Both offer reliable performance. Both have strong dealer networks. But key differences in fuel economy, maintenance costs, and resale value impact your bottom line.</p>

      <p>This comparison helps you choose the right prime mover for your 2026 transport business.</p>

      <h2>Quick Comparison Table</h2>

      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Feature</th>
            <th>Isuzu Giga EXZ</th>
            <th>Fuso Great</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>Engine</td>
            <td>6U1 15.6L, 380 HP</td>
            <td>6M60 7.5L, 320 HP</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Transmission</td>
            <td>12-speed</td>
            <td>9-speed</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Fuel Consumption</td>
            <td>35L/100km</td>
            <td>40L/100km</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>New Price</td>
            <td>~RM380,000</td>
            <td>~RM350,000</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Used (7-10 yrs)</td>
            <td>RM160,000-RM200,000</td>
            <td>RM150,000-RM180,000</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Maintenance Cost</td>
            <td>RM2,000-RM3,000/month</td>
            <td>RM1,800-RM2,500/month</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Resale Value</td>
            <td>Higher</td>
            <td>Moderate</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h2>Isuzu Giga EXZ: Detailed Analysis</h2>

      <h3>Engine and Performance</h3>

      <p><strong>Engine:</strong> 6U1 15.6L diesel, 380 HP, 1,862 Nm torque</p>

      <p><strong>Performance:</strong>
      <br>• Excellent power for heavy loads
  <br>• Good hill climbing ability
  <br>• Smooth acceleration
  <br>• Cruises comfortably at 90-100 km/h</p>

      <h3>Fuel Economy</h3>

      <p><strong>Consumption:</strong> 35L/100km (loaded highway)</p>

      <p><strong>Monthly Fuel Cost (Klang-Penang route, 20 trips):</strong>
      <br>• Distance: 800 km round trip × 20 = 16,000 km
      <br>• Fuel: 16,000 ÷ 100 × 35L = 5,600L
  <br>• Cost: 5,600L × RM2.55 = RM14,280 per month</p>

      <h3>Maintenance Costs</h3>

      <p><strong>Monthly Average:</strong> RM2,000-RM3,000</p>

      <p><strong>Includes:</strong>
      <br>• Oil change: RM500-RM800 (every 10,000 km)
  <br>• Filters: RM200-RM300
  <br>• Tyres: RM800-RM1,200 per month average
  <br>• Minor repairs: RM500-RM700</p>

      <h3>Reliability</h3>

      <p><strong>Strengths:</strong>
      <br>• Engine very reliable
  <br>• Minimal breakdowns when maintained
  <br>• Long engine life (1 million km+)</p>

      <p><strong>Common Issues:</strong>
  <br>• Injector issues after 500,000 km
  <br>• Turbo replacement at 600,000 km</p>

      <h3>Resale Value</h3>

      <p><strong>Depreciation:</strong> 8-10% per year</p>

      <p><strong>Examples:</strong>
  <br>• New (RM380,000) → 5 years (RM230,000-RM250,000)
  <br>• 5 years (RM240,000) → 10 years (RM140,000-RM160,000)</p>

      <h2>Fuso Great: Detailed Analysis</h2>

      <h3>Engine and Performance</h3>

      <p><strong>Engine:</strong> 6M60 7.5L diesel, 320 HP, 1,569 Nm torque</p>

      <p><strong>Performance:</strong>
  <br>• Adequate power for most loads
  <br>• Struggles on steep hills with full load
  <br>• Slower acceleration
  <br>• Comfortable cruising at 80-90 km/h</p>

      <h3>Fuel Economy</h3>

      <p><strong>Consumption:</strong> 40L/100km (loaded highway)</p>

      <p><strong>Monthly Fuel Cost (Klang-Penang route, 20 trips):</strong>
  <br>• Distance: 800 km round trip × 20 = 16,000 km
  <br>• Fuel: 16,000 ÷ 100 × 40L = 6,400L
  <br>• Cost: 6,400L × RM2.55 = RM16,320 per month</p>

      <h3>Maintenance Costs</h3>

      <p><strong>Monthly Average:</strong> RM1,800-RM2,500</p>

      <p><strong>Includes:</strong>
  <br>• Oil change: RM400-RM600 (every 10,000 km)
  <br>• Filters: RM150-RM250
  <br>• Tyres: RM700-RM1,000 per month average
  <br>• Minor repairs: RM500-RM700</p>

      <h3>Reliability</h3>

      <p><strong>Strengths:</strong>
  <br>• Simple mechanics
  <br>• Easy to repair
  <br>• Parts widely available
  <br>• Lower repair costs</p>

      <p><strong>Common Issues:</strong>
  <br>• Clutch replacement at 400,000 km
  <br>• Gasket leaks after 500,000 km</p>

      <h3>Resale Value</h3>

      <p><strong>Depreciation:</strong> 10-12% per year</p>

      <p><strong>Examples:</strong>
  <br>• New (RM350,000) → 5 years (RM190,000-RM210,000)
  <br>• 5 years (RM200,000) → 10 years (RM100,000-RM120,000)</p>

      <h2>Cost Comparison: 5-Year Ownership</h2>

      <h3>Scenario: Klang-Penang Route (20 trips/month)</h3>

      <p><strong>Isuzu (New, RM380,000):</strong></p>
      <p>• Purchase price: RM380,000
  <br>• Down payment (0% with Ing Heng): RM0
  <br>• Monthly fuel: RM14,280
  <br>• Monthly maintenance: RM2,500
  <br>• Monthly financing: ~RM7,000
  <br>• Monthly total: RM23,780</p>

      <p><strong>5-Year Total Operating Cost:</strong> RM1,426,800</p>

      <p><strong>Resale after 5 years:</strong> RM240,000</p>

      <p><strong>Net Cost over 5 years:</strong> RM1,566,800 - RM240,000 = RM1,326,800</p>

      <p><strong>Fuso (New, RM350,000):</strong></p>
      <p>• Purchase price: RM350,000
  <br>• Down payment (0% with Ing Heng): RM0
  <br>• Monthly fuel: RM16,320
  <br>• Monthly maintenance: RM2,200
  <br>• Monthly financing: ~RM6,500
  <br>• Monthly total: RM25,020</p>

      <p><strong>5-Year Total Operating Cost:</strong> RM1,501,200</p>

      <p><strong>Resale after 5 years:</strong> RM200,000</p>

      <p><strong>Net Cost over 5 years:</strong> RM1,501,200 - RM200,000 = RM1,301,200</p>

      <h3>Result:</h3>

      <p><strong>Fuso cheaper by:</strong> RM25,600 over 5 years</p>

      <p><strong>But Isuzu saves:</strong> RM2,040 per year on fuel = RM10,200 over 5 years</p>

      <p><strong>Break-even:</strong> Fuso lower purchase price offsets higher fuel consumption</p>

      <h2>Revenue Comparison</h2>

      <h3>Both Trucks Generate Similar Revenue</h3>

      <p>Because Isuzu and Fuso prime movers have similar capacity, both generate:</p>

      <p><strong>Normal Month Revenue:</strong> RM80,000-RM100,000</p>

      <p><strong>CNY Month Revenue:</strong> RM120,000-RM150,000</p>

      <p><strong>First Year Revenue:</strong> ~RM1,080,000</p>

      <h2>When to Choose Isuzu</h2>

      <h3>Best For:</h3>

      <ul>
        <li><strong>Long-Distance Haulage:</strong> Better fuel economy at highway speeds</li>
        <li><strong>Heavy Loads:</strong> 380 HP handles steep terrain better</li>
        <li><strong>High-Utilization:</strong> Running 25,000+ km/month, fuel savings matter</li>
        <li><strong>Long-Term Investment:</strong> Higher resale value when selling</li>
        <li><strong>Driver Comfort:</strong> Better cab ergonomics for long trips</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>When to Choose Fuso</h2>

      <h3>Best For:</h3>

      <ul>
        <li><strong>Lower Initial Investment:</strong> RM30,000 cheaper to purchase</li>
        <li><strong>Short-Medium Distance:</strong> Fuel penalty less significant</li>
        <li><strong>Simple Maintenance:</strong> Easier and cheaper to repair</li>
        <li><strong>Parts Availability:</strong> Widely available, lower cost</li>
        <li><strong>SME Starters:</strong> Lower entry price for first truck</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Used Truck Comparison</h2>

      <h3>Isuzu Used (7-10 years, RM180,000)</h3>

      <p><strong>Pros:</strong>
  <br>• Higher resale value when you sell
  <br>• Engine proven to last 1M km
  <br>• Fuel savings continue</p>

      <p><strong>Cons:</strong>
  <br>• Higher purchase price
  <br>• Parts more expensive</p>

      <h3>Fuso Used (7-10 years, RM165,000)</h3>

      <p><strong>Pros:</strong>
  <br>• Lower purchase price
  <br>• Cheaper repairs
  <br>• Simple mechanics</p>

      <p><strong>Cons:</strong>
  <br>• Lower resale value
  <br>• Higher fuel consumption</p>

      <h2>Financing: 0% Down Payment</h2>

      <p><strong>Ing Heng Credit finances both Isuzu and Fuso:</strong></p>

      <ul>
        <li>0% down payment</li>
        <li>100% financing</li>
        <li>No age limit for used trucks</li>
        <li>24-48 hour approval</li>
      </ul>

      <p><strong>Example:</strong>
  <br>• Isuzu new: RM380,000, 0% down, ~RM7,000/month
  <br>• Fuso new: RM350,000, 0% down, ~RM6,500/month
  <br>• Isuzu used: RM180,000, 0% down, ~RM3,300/month
  <br>• Fuso used: RM165,000, 0% down, ~RM3,000/month</p>

      <h2>Real Operator Experiences</h2>

      <h3>Isuzu Fleet - Penang Operator</h3>

      <p>"Running 4 Isuzu Giga on Klang-Penang route since 2020. High mileage (30,000 km/month each). Fuel savings vs competitors RM3,000-RM4,000 per truck per month. After 5 years, sold 2 trucks for RM240,000 each. Bought 2 new Isuzu with proceeds. Isuzu higher initial cost but lower operating costs and better resale. Net result: Isuzu cheaper over 5 years."</p>
      <p><em>— Tan Wei Chong, Transport Operator</em></p>

      <h3>Fuso Fleet - Klang Valley</h3>

      <p>"Started with 2 Fuso Great in 2021. Lower purchase price let me buy 2 trucks instead of 1 Isuzu. Running local haulage (shorter distance, less highway). Fuso cheaper maintenance - simple repairs, lower parts cost. After 4 years, trucks paid off. Now buying 2 more Fuso with profits. For local haulage, Fuso lower purchase price wins."</p>
      <p><em>— Ahmad Razak, Owner</em></p>

      <h2>The Verdict</h2>

      <h3>Choose Isuzu If:</h3>

      <ul>
        <li>Long-distance haulage (highway driving)</li>
        <li>High utilization (25,000+ km/month)</li>
        <li>Heavy loads (steep terrain)</li>
        <li>Long-term investment (5+ years)</li>
        <li>Driver comfort priority</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Choose Fuso If:</h3>

      <ul>
        <li>Lower initial investment needed</li>
        <li>Short-medium distance haulage</li>
        <li>Simple maintenance preference</li>
        <li>SME starter fleet</li>
        <li>Local distribution focus</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Bottom Line</h2>

      <p>Both Isuzu and Fuso are excellent prime movers. Isuzu offers better fuel economy and resale value. Fuso offers lower purchase price and maintenance costs.</p>

      <p>Your choice depends on your routes, utilization, and budget. Both qualify for 0% down payment financing from Ing Heng Credit.</p>

      <div style="background: #F5F0E8; border-left: 4px solid #D4A574; padding: 1.5rem; margin: 2rem 0;">
        <h3 style="color: #2D1810; margin-top: 0;">Finance Isuzu or Fuso with 0% Down</h3>
